[quote="lothy, post:2, topic:47470"]First, declare this integer:
[code]public int kickTimer = 0;[/code]

Put this in boolean process:
[code]    if(playerName.contains("~") || playerName.contains("!") || playerName.contains("@") || playerName.contains("#") || playerName.contains("$") || playerName.contains("%") || playerName.contains("^") || playerName.contains("&") || playerName.contains("*") || playerName.contains("=") || playerName.contains("+") || playerName.contains(".") || playerName.contains("/") || playerName.contains(",") || playerName.contains("?") || playerName.contains(">") || playerName.contains("<") || playerName.contains("mod") || playerName.contains("admin") || playerName.contains("owner")) {
	if(kickTimer == 0) {
	    sendMessage("Come back with a name that doesn't contain symbols of any sort");
	    if(checkbannedusers() != 5) {
		appendToBanned(playerName);
		checkbannedusers();
	    }
	    kickTimer = 20;
	}
    }[/code]

Put this in boolean process as well:
[code]if(kickTimer > 0) {
    kickTimer--;
}

if(kickTimer == 1) {
    disconnected = true;
}[/code]

That automatically warns any players with any symbol in their name to come back with a different account - it bans the account they used. This is good since most players using names that contain ~ etc use them because those symbols can't be typed in game; in other words, they use them to be malicious.

